Oct 10 2009 	Great hotel at a good price	We stayed at this hotel during a recent trip to London and Paris. We chose the hotel based on reviews here and the fact that it is not a cookie cutter chain hotel. If you are looking for sleek go elsewhere. The hotel has the authentic ambiance of an old line British hotel. Our room was small by Midwest US standards but was roomy by New York or London standards. The room was immaculately clean and well maintained. The staff was very helpful and friendly. The bar is small but there is an additional room on the opposite side of the bar itself. There is also a lounge near the bar that is quite roomy. The hotel does have a restaurant but we did not use it so we cannot comment on the quality. One drawback is that the hotel is a 10 minute walk from two tube stops. However it is on a very quiet street. There are several pubs and cafes in the area including a well respected fish and chippery. The Wallace Collection is literally across the street although the entrance is one block over on the opposite side from the hotel.We thoroughly enjoyed our stay and will not hesitate to stay here again.	
